CIFS (common Internet fileystem)
connect UNIX server e.g Linux servers to windows shares or smba shares

1.Mounting to a samba from a linux server using CIFS
a. Create mountpoint
#mkdir /cifsmnt
#mount -t cifs //192.168.2.73/fullbackup /cifsmnt -o username=student,password=school1

2. Mounting to a windows share from a linux server using cifs
on windows system ,you have to enable file and print sharing
#mkdir /cifsmnt1
#mount -t cifs //192.168.1.251/Users /cifsmnt1 -o username=unix6,password=school1
